In these cases, per-word replacement can lead to explosion of rules.
Furthermore, tagging rules should be inferred automatically.
We solve GEC using a non-autoregressive approach, in which
we predict character-based transformation for every (sub)word.
The transformations are constructed automatically from data.
We consider four kinds of transformations:
• keep token, replace token, append token before/after
• string-at-word: string transformations applied on complete words
• string-at-subword: string transformations applied on subwords

3. for bert-uncased, diacritics added by diacritization edit script
• char-at-word: character transformations applied on words
• char-at-subword: character transformations applied on subwords
